	- `loss, model, opt_state = make_step(_ts, yi, model, opt_state)`
		- the *learning signal* comes from the mean squared error over all timepoints between a predicted trajectory and the true trajectory.
		- `_ts`
			- it is about the *training strategy*: basically first you train the model only on the first 10% of trajectory length, then you train it on the full trajectories
			- == `ts[: int(length_size * length)]`
				- ts == timeticks of trajectories in the dartaset (eg linspace(0, 10, 100))
				- length_size == trajectory length
				- length == float in length_strategy
					- length_strategy=(0.1, 1)
		- `yi`
			- it is a batch of trajectories shape(batch_size, time_ticks, dimensions) sampled from the data pool; all 
			- == value from list generated by `dataloader((_ys,), batch_size, key=loader_key`
			- `dataloader`
				- all it does is return batches of objects from your datapool.
